    {
      "label": "Further remarks",
      "value": "We can deduct from the missing words in lines one and two that about half of the papyrus is missing on the right side. This assumption is supported by the fact that half of the address on the verso has disappeared."
    },
    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "Recto: The basmala seems to be missing from the beginning of the letter, while the opening formulae seem to be complete (l. 1). The second line starts with an invocation that usually followed a remark about the health of the writer (l. 3). The text exhibits unconventional ligatures. \nThe sender mentions that he has written two lectures for the addressee about al-Fustat (l. 2). He also refers to freights (ll. 5; 6). "
    },
    {
      "label": "Diacritical dots",
      "value": "There is one diacritical dot in line 3. In several places unconventional ligatures occur."
    }
